<dl id="n09018b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09018b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09018b"> 18(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> utilitarian</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Condorcets, Benthams, and Marxs of the future will I think be as ruthlessly critical of the metaphysics and ethics of their times as were their predecessors, but not quite so sure of their own; they will lack a certain heaviness of touch which we may note in <mark>Utilitarianism</mark> and Socialism. <small> J. B. S. Haldane, <a name="DAED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DAED"><cite title="source">Dedalus</cite></a> (1923) 17</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
